For the clustering analyses and outlier tests done by AQM we use the variance-stabilizing transform from DESeq2(Love, Huber, and Anders 2014) package. The variance-stabilizing transform has the same purpose as taking the log, to rescale the data because of the large spread in gene expression counts. Since we can’t take the log of counts of zero we use an alternative method.

Array Quality Metrics

In this section an Array Quality Metrics report (AQM) is generated using the arrayQualityMetrics package from Bioconductor.(Kauffmann, Gentleman, and Huber 2009) This report does some basic analyses like PCA and three sample outlier detection tests originally intended for MicroArray data but still suitable to gene expression data. The analyses done using this out-of-the-box array quality metrics report are very general and only give an indication of possible outliers, however these are common methods that are easily explained.

The output of this section is an .html file in the sub-folder of the report directory. This file is also linked in the final report in this section but may also be opened by opening the .html file directly from your file explorer.
